  "description": "An Incentive Program is a package of incentive-related services and/or benefits, accompanied by defined terms and conditions, that is offered as a whole to internal or external customers to reward product usage, customer behavior, or relationship value.\r\n\r\nComment:\r\nAn incentive program in banking refers to a strategy used by banks and financial institutions to encourage specific behaviors from customers or employees by offering rewards or benefits.\r\n- Incentive programs in banking can be considered a type of product when they are designed as structured offerings with defined terms, benefits, and objectives-especially when aimed at customers to encourage specific financial behaviors.",
